==English==

===Etymology===
{{F.}} ''super'' from {{L.}} ''[[supra]]'', see [[super-]].

===Pronunciation===
{{audio|En-ca-super.ogg|Audio (CA)}}
*(General): so͞o'pə(r), /ˈsuːpə(r)/, /"su:p@(r)/
*{{UK}}: /'sju:p@/
*{{US}}: /ˈsupɚ/, /"sup@`/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-uːpə(r)|Rhymes: -uːpə(r)]]
SOO-per or SU-per

===Adjective===
{{en-adj-notcomp}}

# [[better]] than average, better than usual; [[wonderful]].

